column3: Avoid use of the words “all,” “never” and “always.”

In case your colleague is handling multiple roles, you could give differentiated feedback 
(e.g. as engineer in your subsystem/CP/QR/ScrumMaster/SPO/CO/FCO/SME/TS/etc.)
Constructive feedback is information-specific, issue-focused, and based on observations.

column2: Be direct when delivering your message.
column3: Both negative and positive feedback should be given in a straightforward manner.

column2: Be sincere and avoid giving mixed messages.
column3: Sincerity says that you mean what you say with care and respect.

column2: In positive feedback situations, express appreciation.
In negative feedback situations, express concern.
column3:
A tone of concern communicates a sense of importance and care and provides the appropriate level of sincerity to the message.
The purpose of negative feedback is to create awareness that can lead to correction or improvement in performance.
Tell what you've noticed, not what you think of it, and report the behavior you notice at a concrete level, instead of as a characterization of the behavior.
The information should be about your own perception of information, not about the other’s perceptions, assumptions and motives.
Achieving individual objectives and fulfilling individual tasks
An employee’s effectiveness at improving others’ performance and using others’ contributions to improve his or her own performance.

column2: Networking / Sharing and Learning from Others

column3: prioritizes activities based on organizational goals and self-directs work. Possesses extensive knowledge of own and other teams' strategic business priorities
coordinates one’s work and performance with that of others to achieve mutual outcomes
understands the informal structures and decision-making processes of the organization
identifies problems and opportunities for changes and implements solutions when appropriate. Challenges the status quo and initiates substantial change
positive role model, able to highly motivate individuals and teams to achieve outstanding results
